quizzes.question:
Add the box shadow property for a result of 10 pixels vertical offset, 20 pixels horizontal offset, and red for the color.
[!raw!]
{0}: {1}px {2}px red;

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The box-shadow Property[/h1]

The CSS3 [b]box-shadow[/b] property applies shadow to elements.
Components of the box-shadow property are decoded by browsers in the following manner:
- The first length for the [b]horizontal offset[/b] will cast the shadow to the right of the box (required)
- The second length is for the [b]vertical offset[/b] that will cast the shadow to below the box (required)
- The [b]color[/b] of the shadow (optional)

In the example below, the horizontal and vertical offsets have been set to 10px:[code format="css" codeId="583"]div {
   width: 300px;
   height: 100px;
   background-color: #9ACD32;
   [b]box-shadow: 10px 10px #888888;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2669" width="100%"]
